-- Shanghai Government Expects 2010 Home Sales to Fall `Sharply' on Year Ago
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-02T07:32:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/shanghai-government-expects-2010-home-sales-to-fall-sharply-on-year-ago.html

          
          
             Shanghai’s new home sales this year
are expected to fall “sharply” from 2009, Zhou Bo, head of
Shanghai Municipal Development & Reform Commission said in a
statement on the planning body’s website.  
 Shanghai new home sales in the first half fell 35.8 percent
from a year ago to 10.09 million square meters, acccording to
the statement.  
